                            <comment id="17464009" author="dsmiley" created="Wed, 22 Dec 2021 18:54:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s striking to me how this test class suddenly started failing at around December 13th:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://fucit.org/solr-jenkins-reports/history-trend-of-recent-failures.html#series/org.apache.solr.cloud.OverseerCollectionConfigSetProcessorTest.testReplicationEqualNumberOfSlicesPerNodeSendCreateNodesEqualToLiveNodesDistributedUpdates&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://fucit.org/solr-jenkins-reports/history-trend-of-recent-failures.html#series/org.apache.solr.cloud.OverseerCollectionConfigSetProcessorTest.testReplicationEqualNumberOfSlicesPerNodeSendCreateNodesEqualToLiveNodesDistributedUpdates&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
(we are so lucky to have this tool to help us; thank you &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=hossman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;hossman&quot;&gt;hossman&lt;/a&gt;!)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When I look at our commit history at this point and prior, it&apos;s not clear what happened around then that I could imagine might impact this test.  Maybe I&apos;m not thinking creatively enough about it at the moment.  &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-15843&quot; title=&quot;Update Log4J dependency&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-15843&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-15843&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-15804&quot; title=&quot;Unable to view XML files via the Solr Collection GUI&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-15804&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-15804&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-15745&quot; title=&quot;Rewrite v2 core-admin APIs using annotation framework&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-15745&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-15745&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17464089" author="houston" created="Wed, 22 Dec 2021 21:35:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I believe it actually has to do with this change: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-15803&quot; title=&quot;Allow AssignStrategy to process multiple AssignRequests with cross-coordination&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-15803&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-15803&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Basically the replicas used to be assigned to nodes in the order the nodes were sent, if they were sent. However starting with this ticket, the nodes are sorted based on how good of a fit for the replica they are, and then replicas are assigned to the nodes sorted at the beginning.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll try fixing this up, though it is very weird that I can&apos;t reproduce it locally.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17464093" author="houston" created="Wed, 22 Dec 2021 21:53:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok added a PR that removes the need for the nodeList to be used in the order its given. Now the test just checks that each replica in a shard uses a unique node, and that the node is in the given nodeList.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17464149" author="dsmiley" created="Wed, 22 Dec 2021 22:56:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for looking into this Houston!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe we can&apos;t trust the precision of the dates in the chart too much.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17464153" author="jira-bot" created="Wed, 22 Dec 2021 23:09:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit fdfe0c3d93e9d7c19ed195f19e61eee402e4e1dd in solr&apos;s branch refs/heads/main from Houston Putman&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=fdfe0c3&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=fdfe0c3&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-15868&quot; title=&quot;Frequent OverseerCollectionConfigSetProcessorTest failures&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-15868&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-15868&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Fix test broken by new sorting of nodeList (#471)&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="17464154" author="houston" created="Wed, 22 Dec 2021 23:09:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We can leave this open to make sure the tests start to pass on Jenkins.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17464418" author="janhoy" created="Thu, 23 Dec 2021 10:28:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We had one successful run &lt;a href=&quot;https://ci-builds.apache.org/job/Solr/job/Solr-Check-main/2441/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://ci-builds.apache.org/job/Solr/job/Solr-Check-main/2441/&lt;/a&gt; and the two runs after it did not contain that test failure, even if they failed due to other tests. Think you can close this. Thanks for the fix!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17464749" author="hossman" created="Thu, 23 Dec 2021 18:41:45 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Maybe we can&apos;t trust the precision of the dates in the chart too much.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From the chart description...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;This graph shows the historic failure rates &amp;#8211; at a per-week granularity &amp;#8211; ...&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So the week starting with 2021-12-06 saw 0% failures, but the week starting with 2021-12-13 saw 13% failures, and the week starting with 2021-12-20 has seen 21% failures &lt;em&gt;so far&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17535655" author="janhoy" created="Thu, 12 May 2022 00:26:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing after the 9.0.0 release&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
